      <item>
        <title>Mercenary and sellsword</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Sketch]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <aside class="quote no-group" data-username="NOBLE1" data-post="50" data-topic="71474">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="https://www.ThroneOfLies.com/images/class-icons/princess-icon-256.jpg" class="avatar"> NOBLE1:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>Can you explain why this is so bad? Say you don’t have a bad player, then what? Or even if you do have a bad player or a new player that you have to be a little smarter with to help keep alive.</p>
<p>Again even if you lose early on then just wait to join another game.</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>Losing because of bad BD is one thing, but losing because of a single player’s actions feels a lot worse. Your winrate is tied to a single player instead of a team of 8-9 players. There is no single decision that BD can make that causes a loss. Mistakes are remedied by successes and with so many minds working towards your win, you have a lot of lee-way.</p>
<p>The implied volatility of a Merc’s winrate would skyrocket if they relied on a single person to win.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Again even if you lose early on then just wait to join another game.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>“Just join a new game for when you lose” does not make players feel better that their target screwed up royally.</p>
          <p><a href="https://forum.throneoflies.com/t/mercenary-and-sellsword/71474/76">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
